	  we do not need to redesign them.

2003-06-17 15:06  khoang82

	* edit.php: Fix: [ 694688 ] better permission scheme Resolution:
	  Originally, the permission select boxes in edit.php are to show
	  users who has certain right to the chosen file.  However, when
	  the admin alter anything on this page and submit, there is no way
	  to figure out which of these users where specifically given their
	  rights and which one got theirs through inheriting it.  So the
	  new design for this page will both more straight forward for the
	  user and the programmers.  The permission select boxes are now
	  used to directly specify which user has which right to the file.
	  Admin needs not to set inheriting rights.  When the admin sets
	  rights to the department, he indirectly set inheriting rights for
	  all users.

